host_about: Historian, reporter, editor, literary author. Leading lyricist of the band Poets Don't Dance. Born in 1970 in an industrial town in Holland, Serge van Duijnhoven came to literature via post-industrial culture, through an interest in contemporary history, sociology and anthropology. He loves to combine words and music, and has included CDs along with some of his works of fiction and non-fiction.  Van Duijnhoven worked as a war-correspondent in Sarajevo, won the “Nova Malekodonia” prize in Struga, Makedonia in 1995, and was one of the passengers on board the train “Literature Express Europe 2000” that carried 104 writers from all over the continent through numerous cities and countries. Currently he lives and works in Brussels on a book of history about World War I, and on a novel about the vanishing meaning of trusted social values in a hyper-accelerated world of materialism and individuality. In the spring of 2012, SvD lived and worked as writer-in-residence in the city  of Yerevan, Armenia, where he wrote a CITYBOOK during the Unesco World Book Capital Ceremonies, and gave a concert with his band DDN in commemoration of the Armenian Genocide. As a gifted storyteller, Serge van Duijnhoven is known to embark regularly on literary excursions through the city of Brussels during which he passionately evokes the many peculiar tales of life from legendary passengers like Voltaire, Karl Marx, Victor Hugo, Alexandre Dumas, Baudelaire, Multatuli, Arthur Rimbaud... All of whom, fleeing tyranny or debt, found a refuge in the cozy streets and corners of this peasantly simplistic, pleasantly grotesque and genuinely bilingual city.

host_about: Hola Soy Coco   Soy una mujer Venezolana que se la pasa viajando con su Esposo por todo el mundo.Apenas dispongo de dinero y tiempo reservo un vuelo.  Disfrutamos la vida plenamente asi que les les doy la Bienvenida a todos los turistas que quieran sentir una experiencia novedosa y llena de agradables sorpresas que se sientan en su casa, comodos, tranquilos y felices.  Pienso que en este mundo de avanzada en tecnología, industrialización y contaminación, el mejor polo a tierra es vivir rodeado de la Pacha Mama; es por esto que me gusta compartir mi refugio. Me gusta la vida tranquila, en donde interactuar con el otro se fundamente en el respeto, la comprensión y la armonia. Soy muy nutricia por exelencia, es así, que cuando preparo los alimentos lo hago pensando en el beneficio que traerá al cuerpo ingerirlos; porque son preparados con condimentos naturales y amor. La lectura es uno de mis hobbys preferidos porque a traves de ella puedo viajar en el tiempo, conocer otras culturas y sobre todo reconocerme en un libro. OSHO, Riana Eisler, Walt Whitman, Khalil Gibran, Victor E. Frank, Rodolfo Llinas y nuestro nobel de literatura Gabriel García Marquez, entre muchos por mencionar algunos me han enseñado que la vida vale la pena vivirla, solo si tienes capacidad de servicio y es ese el fundamento del hospedaje que brindo aqui un servicio íntegro - familiar.   Coco

Nous aimons Bruxelles et sa multi-culturalité. Ensemble, nous partageons 4 nationalités et avons vécu dans 4 pays différents.  Travaillant pour une télévision, je suis au coeur de l'événement, et je partage avec beaucoup de plaisir tous ces sujets. Une de mes passions est "très belge" : je collectionne les bandes dessinées. Depuis toujours je cours les librairies, bouquinistes, marchés aux puces et parfois salles de ventes pour trouver les perles rares. Si vous le voulez, je pourrais vous faire découvrir mes "coups de coeur". Les petites choses qui embellissent ma vie ici : aller au marché au bas de ma rue le samedi et/ou le dimanche, y acheter des fleurs et partager une assiette d'huitres et un verre de vin blanc avec ma compagne et les amis du quartier; Refaire le monde dans les bistrots du quartier avec les amis. Me promener au bord des étangs et à l'abbaye de la Cambre avec mon chien après une journée de travail. host_about: Hello and welcome!   I am Jennifer!   If you are looking an apartment in Liege or Brussels, you are on the right page! No matter the length of your stay, we have a number of apartments to show you in either Liege or Brussels. Whether you are considering a romantic getaway, a family vacation or a business trip, we have what you need!   Most of our apartments are located in the heart of downtown, steps away from public transportation, shopping, bars and restaurants.  I happened to create Ze Agency’s after living a few years abroad. I wanted people to discover Belgium the way I know her and as local citizens.  I realized that living in an apartment is the perfect way to get used to a country, a neighborhood, and little local shops. It is the best way to feel at home! This is why, once back in 2009, I started Ze Agency.  What I particularly like about Ze Agency is the unique and human relationship I have with each member of the community.  The work environment is fantastic, authentic and very friendly. Once a week, we have breakfast together and talk about everything, from our little lives to the overall work. We want everyone to feel good and enjoy working in the agency.  We have an excellent relationship with our tenants.  Trust is everywhere: from their accommodations they happily entrusted to us to the reliable information they receive from us as experts of the market. We do our best to make their goods profitable. I’m quite sure they enjoy our services!  What I love about Liege is its convivial, caring, relax and festive side. Being “Liégeois” is a synonym for being a “party boy or girl”.  I love Brussels for is its international and multicultural side. Different languages can be heard during a day and you are certain to meet worldwide people on the city capital! This aspect can be seen in the melting pot of affordable restaurants in the city. Least but not last, a very friendly Belgian welcoming always present!  We are very much looking forward to sharing our great tips with you!  We hope that you will love your stay with us.   Soon,  Jennifer, Sophie & Ze Agency Team.

Bonjour,   Je suis française originaire de Lyon et travaille actuellement en Belgique dans un groupe industriel. J'ai 25 ans, je suis très dynamique et sociable et pour moi rien n'est meilleur que lorsque l'on partage !  Je suis d'un naturel très joyeux, mais suis très portée sur le respect et l’honnêteté que je considère comme la base de toutes relations ! C'est sûrement pour cela qu'en général je suis considérée comme une personne de confiance.  J'ai toujours aimé recevoir et faire en sorte que mes invités se sentent chez eux et que les choses se fassent "naturellement".  J'aime voyager, je suis déjà partie pour des vacances, des expériences pro ou pour de l'humanitaire dans plusieurs pays en Europe, en Amérique Latine et en Amérique du Nord, et aimerais prochainement découvrir l'Asie du sud est. Etant lyonnaise, j'adore la bonne gastronomie (bonne vivante oblige!). Et j'adore l'Art dans son intégralité: musique, danse, peinture, sculpture, théatre, etc.  Alors à bientôt (chez moi ou chez vous ! )

We are Shari (the lady) and Aïssa (the guy); yes… our names can get pretty confusing. -> We do blame that entirely on our parents though! ;-)  Shari: I am originally from the flemish part of Belgium and live in Brussels for several years now. I have moved a fair bit throughout the years and I never thought I would say this: I totally fell in love with this city! It has a very multicultural and dynamic feel without losing it's warmth and genuine charm. I have a quite bubbly personality and love to get to know new people. Oh, yes I also looove chocolate and salsa dancing ;-) My motto in life would be: If you can imagine it, you can make it happen !!  Aïssa: I am born in Brussels and settled down here after discovering some other parts of the world. I have a calm and friendly personality and love to disappear in my thoughts to find new ways of doing things. And yes, I do have a tendency to sneak away with Shari's chocolate (shht don't tell her..) but make up for it on the dance floor ;-) My motto in life would be: Do it to the best of your abilities, or don't do it at all !!  Business wise both of us are active in the field of marketing and appreciate the art of beautiful and well presented things.  One of the many passions we share is traveling. We love to discover new places and we prefer to do so in style and comfort. This is why we aim to offer exactly that to every person staying with us. We hope you will enjoy !! :-)  Shari & Aïssa

I’m David, a 30 years old boy living in the wonderful capital of Europe. I can say I m curious, adventurous and always looking for new challenges.  At the age of 10 I started colllecting photos of countries around the world cut in old magazines. I would call the ambassy and other tourism offices to ask for brochures they could send home (internet wasn’t popular at that time).  When I turned 18, my parents offered me the opportunity to spend one schoolyear in California.  After 2 months of hard work cleaning offices windows during the summer holiday, I was in L.A. ! (No need to tell you how fun it was…)  Since then, I travelled the world ; hiked on the Lofoten Island, gardened in Woody Allen’s house in New York, partied under the Hollywood Sign in Los Angeles, taught English at the Chiang Mai University, met Santa Claus in Finland, rode a bike in the empty streets of Paris and most important : I met many great people.  To keep these memories alive, i always bring along my photocamera and a notebook in which I write down my feelings (It is always fun to reread the notes a few year after). I also love making short movies of my holidays and invite my friends over to show them what they've missed.  According to my experience, the most unique destination would be Asia. I ve only been to Thailand but from what I ve seen and heard, Laos, Cambodge, Japan, Malaysia, China, Indonesia are very tempting places to discover.  I also love wandering around in a city avoiding the tourist crowd and looking for the most authentic places to be.  I remember that old lady we met in a lavatory in San Francisco. She happened to be an ex stewardess for the Panam company ! We ended up talking the whole evening. Unforgettable !   What I expect from the Airbnb experience is to dive into the culture of a country by staying in an actual residential area, meeting its owner and sharing some tips about the city I will visit or simply talking about life while cooking a good meal.   Cheers

J'aimerait collaborer avec des musiciens pour mettre en valeur mon répertoire. Je suis passionnée par les destins, les gens dont je croise le chemin. Mon compagnon (comédien) et moi recevons  des hôtes depuis juillet 2013 pour des périodes de quelques mois et nous nous réjouissons de ces expériences chaque fois différentes. Nous aimons également voyager(dernièrement l'Andalousie). Chez nous vous trouverez une ambiance calme et des règles de vie simples. Ah oui ! Nous parlons Anglais!

host_about: Nous avons deux petites filles et habitons au Beguinage depuis 5 ans. Nous nous sommes rencontrés au détour d’un voyage d’affaire à Bucarest. Voyager fait partie de nos gênes et on a du mal à tenir en place ! Mus est un vrai ras des villes, il est fan de voitures anciennes, déniche les petits bars à vins branchouilles, pratique le squash et la course à pieds et est un habitué des ‘working-coffee-bar’ du quartier. Caroline a grandi au vert mais aime la vie urbaine, elle est passionnée d’art contemporain, passe des heures sur les blogs culinaires, joue au tennis et travaille dans le secteur des soins de santé. Nous sommes tous les deux des passionnés de voyages, fans de citytrips, avides de découvertes culinaires et toujours à la recherche du dernier spot tendance déniché sur l’un ou l’autre blog !  We have 2 little girls and live in the 'Beguinage' since 5 years. We met with the turning of a business trip in Bucharest. Travel is part of our genes! Mus is a real flush of cities, he is a fan of old-timers, unearths small trendy wine bars, plays squash and do run.  He is also a regular of the 'working-coffee-bar' in the area Caroline grew green but loves city life, she is passionate about contemporary art, spends hours on culinary blogs, plays tennis and works in the healthcare sector. We are both travel enthusiasts, fans of city trips, eager for culinary discoveries and always looking for the latest trendy spots unearthed on either blog.

Hi there!  I'm Bruno and I've been living in Brussels for a couple of years now. I've become a very experienced airbnb host over the past year and as you will see from my reviews I've been doing a pretty good job at it :-)   I speak English, Dutch and French fluently. I'm rather well acquainted with Brussels, its restaurants and cafés, the things you have to see and how to get there, so I think that's a big asset for my guests. I love popping a bottle of wine and just talk about life and exchange experiences. I'm a giver not a taker, very sociable, understanding, empathic, rather smily. :-)  A last thing I'd like to mention before you finish reading about me is that I'm gay. It's not something that dominates my life, but I do however only want to accommodate people that are fine with homosexuals and do not have any traditional or religious objections against it. In other words: I don't want people in my house who hate people like me. I think that's only fair, right?  I think that was it for my introduction! See you soon?  Bruno

Welcome!  We live in Brussels and we are managing a property management service for short-term location.   If you are looking for an apartment to rent in Brussels, you are contacting the right people! No matter the length or the purpose of your stay, many properties are put at your disposal for you to find the right place.  Renting a property is without a doubt the best way to discover a city. You are directly immerse in the daily life of the locals which allow you to have a neighborhood life and discover the city from a new perspective.    Welcoming of guests and services are personalized in order to give a top-notch service and ensures that you will enjoy your stay at its best.  All our properties are provided with: wifi connection, cotton sheets, towels, kitchen tea towels, essentials (tea, coffee, shampoo) and have a exclusive travel guide which gives you Brussel’s best addresses.  BnBetter was born out of a common passion for travels and human relationships. We have a great sense of hospitality and well being and therefore have great relationships with hosts and guests.   We are dynamic, innovative and passionate about what we do. We speak English, French and Dutch and will answer all your questions with great pleasure!   We hope you will enjoy your stay with us.  Pauline & Dorothée.

We are dynamic, innovative and passionate about what we do. We speak English, French and Dutch and will answer all your questions with great pleasure!   We hope you will enjoy your stay with us.  Pauline & Dorothée.

host_about: Hello !  I am Adrien, born and raised in Brussels and I have to admit that I'm in love with my city! I'm really proud to live in what I consider the cosmopolitan capital of Belgium. What do I love about it ? It’s little streets, it’s hidden spots, and the unique things that  make it the very center of Europe. It’s always a great pleasure for me to assist travelers in discovering my city. That’s the reason why I’ve decided to transform this passion into my job, by working for Sweet Inn. Sweet Inn provides amazing vacation apartments in Brussels – spacious, stylish and perfectly located - with all the services and comfort of a hotel. Oh, and there’s also a Sweet Inn Lobby located on Avenue Louise where my team and myself  will cater to your every need and make sure you experience the best of the city during your stay. Even away from home, you will feel at home.  I’ll personally wait for you at your apartment to welcome you and to hand you the keys.   I will be more than happy to provide you some tips to experience the best of my city. Where to go to dinner? Where to drink the best beer or to savor the best waffle? Where to buy the best chocolates ? Which museum to visit ?  With my recommendations you have no excuse not to leave Brussels without having seen the best and coolest local spots. So why hesitate? Just book and come to explore Brussels like a local!  I am Adrien and I’m looking forward to hosting you ;)  --------------------------------------  Bonjour !  Je suis Adrien, et j'ai chance d'être né et d'avoir grandi dans la splendide ville de Bruxelles, et je dois bien avouer que je suis amoureux de ma ville ! Je suis très fier d'habiter dans la ville que je considère la plus cosmopolite d'Europe. Ce que j'aime le plus ? Me perdre à travers ses rues, visiter ses petits coins cachés, et bien évidemment ses habitants ! Et j’ai encore tellement de choses à partager sur cette ville que je connais par coeur, alors n'hésitez pas à me poser des questions, je me ferai une joie de vous conseiller sur quoi faire dans ma merveilleuse ville ! Comme vous pouvez le voir j’ai une réelle passion pour Bruxelles, c’est pourquoi j’ai décidé de faire de cette passion mon métier, en intégrant la géniale équipe de Sweet Inn. Le concept de Sweet Inn permet de louer des appartements de vacances à Bruxelles (et dans plusieurs autres villes du Monde) - spacieux, décorés par nos architectes d’intérieurs locaux, et toujours idéalement situés.  Oh, et il y a aussi un Lobby Sweet Inn situé sur l’avenue Louise où mon équipe et moi-même nous feront une joie de vous guider et de vous conseiller pour que vous profitiez au maximum de votre séjour.  Il est très important pour moi que les gens qui résident dans un appartement Sweet Inn se sentent chez eux. Le meilleur restaurant pour aller dîner ? Où trouver la meilleure bière ou bien déguster la gaufre la plus savoureuse? Où acheter les meilleurs chocolats ? Quel musée visiter absolument ? Avec mes conseils vous n'aurez aucune excuse pour quitter la ville sans avoir visiter ses meilleurs endroits, même ceux que seuls les vrais Bruxellois connaissent ;) Je vous livre un accueil personnel, toujours avec le sourire, et je serai toujours à votre disposition, que cela soit pour vous livrer les meilleurs bons plans ou tout simplement en cas de besoin. Alors pourquoi hésiter ? Vous n'avez qu'à réserver pour explorer cette ville, avec tous les conseils d'un local !  Je suis Adrien. Bienvenue chez moi.  Hâte de vous accueillir ;)

Hello!   We are two young professionals both working in Brussels. We have been living for 3 years in the apartment, we loved it there, but had to move as we are now a little family with 2 young babies. However we live at 5min from the apartment, because we love the area. From Thieffry you can get anywhere you want in a no-time, you have all the shops and restaurants you need and it is oh so quiet at night.  We love to travel, after our wedding we have been travelling around the world for a few months. We love to meet new people, exchange ideas and experiences and have a great time with them. Ps: notre life motto is "passion changes everything"  Kind regards, Barbara and Alex

This is your life. Do what you love and do it often. If you don’t like something, change it. If you don’t like your job, quit. If you don’t have enough time, stop watching tv. If you’re looking for the love of your life, stop.  They will be waiting for you when you start doing the things you love. When you eat, appreciate every last bite. Open your mind, arms, and heart to new things and people. We are united in our differences. Ask the next person you see what their passion is, And share your inspiring dream with them. Travel often, getting lost will help you find yourself. Some opportunities only come once, seize them. Life is about the people you meet, And the things you create with them. So go out and start creating. Life is short.  Live your dream and wear your passion.

In 2014 werden Filip en ik verliefd op een huis in wat bekend staat als één van de mooiste straten van Antwerpen.  We besloten er onze eigen woning van te maken, maar ook om drie vakantiewoningen te voorschijn te toveren om anderen te laten meegenieten van deze uitzonderlijke locatie in het historische centrum. Filip, niet toevallig architect, liet zijn tekenkunsten op het huis los en vandaag zijn we eindelijk in de mogelijkheid om gasten te ontvangen.  Als fervente reizigers hopen we nu ook zelf anderen te kunnen helpen bij het ontdekken van onze lievelingsstad: Antwerpen!!  Samen spreken we bovendien vijf verschillende talen, dus kom ons gerust aan een taalproef onderwerpen...

In addition, I try to keep my cultural horizons open by visiting museums/exhibitions (we do have some really nice ones in Belgium) and various events as well as eating out and tasting our lovely Belgian cuisine offered in many restaurants.

Hello,  We are very happy to welcome you in all our apartments located rue du Lombard or avenue Huart Hamoir. Gael is born in Brazil and lives in Belgium since 7 years and speaks French, Portuguese, English, Spanish, Italian and Dutch. I have lived in London, Paris, and I speak French and English. We look very much forward to meeting you, let's hope these apartments will tempt you !

I am an experienced "home exchanger" (more than 40 exchanges all over Europe) and like to make people feel "at home" in my house. I like good food and good wine, walking in the nature, flea markets, design, typography. My motto could be "always look on the bright side of life". You will most probably meet my youngest son Virgile (he loves computer games, he speaks Dutch and French), maybe my other son Jonas (fan of the Barca, able to make you mint tea the moroccan way), or my partner Ronald (he lives in the countryside, that's the reason why I am seldom at home in Brussels)

Je m'appelle Michael, j'ai 36 ans et habite Bruxelles, à Saint-Gilles. Une ville pleine d'artistes et d'animations.  J'ai 2 passions : Les massages (Passion et métier en même temps) et le voyage. J'adore voyager avec Airbnb, m'offrir des belles locations d'appartements, maisons, villas de logement à des prix très intéréssants. J'ai déjà voyager en Pologne, Espagne, Inde, Thaïlande, Grèce, Italie, Irlande, Portugal, Etats-Unis, Canada et plein d'autre encore. Découvrir la manière dont vivent les gens dans chaque endroit du monde me passionne.

Hello all, My brother and I share our beautiful apartment in Brussels centre. It is a very spacious place in the buzzy heart of Brussels! Ideal to discover the city (near main museums, train station, the Grand Place, etc). The flat has its own phone line with free unlimited calls. The kitchen is equipped with a big fridge, freezer, dishwasher, oven, coffee machine, micro-wave, and various accessories and machines for fine cooking. Additionally, there is an extra 20-square-meters storage room in the basement of the building. The flat is just behind La Monnaie/De Munt, 1min away from De Brouckère station (easy connection for all metro, tram and bus lines), 5mins away from Brussels Central Railway station. All main shops (Delhaize, Brico, Carrefour, Fnac, Media Markt, Schleiper, Pain Quotidien,…) are within minuts of reach.  While I'm having an internship in London, I'm subletting my room. Please, get in touch!

My career  took me away 6 years ago to make me tour the world! Based in Montreal and traveling the globe on a regular basis, I enjoy making a stopover in Brussels every possible time! If home is where the heart is, then it is in Brussels, and you'll easily understand why once you have discovered its many hidden gems!  There is definitely much more to Brussels than waffles, chocolate and beers, but those are already good reasons to plan your next trip there! :-)  Send me your request and I'll be more than happy to help plan this trip and make it a great one!  Looking forward to reading from you very soon! D.

We are a young married professional couple. I am Australian and my wife is Belgian. We met in Brussels and are leaving in the neighborhood for 4 years. We love to travel, meet new people, make new friends and to have new experiences.

Hi!   My name is Marit. I was born and raised in Belgium as the granddaughter of an Italian mineworkers family. I live in Antwerp, which is one of the nicest cities in Belgium to visit.   I have a 7 year old son, Ernesto. He is the cutest boy ever. I love the area Antwerpen-Berchem. If you have some imagination, you could compare it to Williamsburg in New York once in a while. Let me know if I can be of any help to you in exploring these areas of the city!   Along with some good friends working in advertising, I once published a cook book, a collection of easy-to-make recipes created by my mum, the best "mammina" in the world. It has been rewarded with 2 Gourmand World Cookbook Awards, for Best Concept and Best Italian Cookbook. Yes, I love good food and travelling. Don't hesitate to ask me a list with great actual exhibitions and musea, or a list with the best restaurants in Antwerp, based on your preferences. Asian, Belgian, Indonesian, ... restaurants, or simply the best Belgian fries ... you can all find them here, on a stone's throw :-)

Salut Ana, Ivo et moi vivons à Bruxelles.   Elle est argentine. Il est mi argentin - mi belge. Je suis belge.   Elle est danseuse, professeure de pilâtes et de gyrotonic. Agé de 5 ans, il est très habile, créatif et passionné de ninjas. Je suis anthropologue et comédien. Je me passionne pour le yoga.   Ana et Ivo partent en Argentine pour une visite familiale. Moi, je retape un appartement que je viens d'acheter. Je pourrai vous accueillir, vous conseiller et vous aider mais je ne vivrai pas dans l'appartement.   Vous serez donc libres, libres, libres !  Cet agréable appartement de +/- 100 m2 est idéal pour une famille avec deux enfants, un couple d'amoureux ou 4 amis.   Il y a un lit double dans une chambre, un lit superposé dans une seconde, une salle de bain, un wc, un salon, une cuisine et un balcon.   Il y a le Wifi.   Le calme est assuré.   Le voisinage est vraiment sympa.   Situé à proximité de deux parcs, le quartier est trouve au sommet de Bruxelles.  Non loin d'ici, la vue est impressionnante !   Il y a de nombreux petits commerces, de diverses possibilités pour se déplacer en  transports en communs. L'appartement est à seulement 20 minutes du centre.

host_about: Alix, Louise, et moi habitons Bruxelles depuis toujours. Nous adorons notre ville, pour sa taille humaine et sa nature hyper cosmopolite. Voyageurs du monde, nous constatons après chaque voyage combien Bruxelles est unique, et proche de villes telles New-York ou Londres pour son caractère international.  Et, ce qui ajoute à son agrément, il s'y passe quelquechose tous les jours: concerts, événements populaires, théâtre, danse... Notre quartier est l'un des plus calmes et appréciés des bruxellois : en bordure de forêt, de nombreux transports en commun à proximité pour nous déplacer, et de nombreux commerces et restaurants. Nous apprécions néanmoins nous déplacer, majoritairement, en vélo. Ce n'est pas pour rien que ce quartier est très prisé des bruxellois et de toute personne qui désire s'installer à Bruxelles. Nous aurons à coeur de vous faire apprécier votre séjour, au calme et dans la chaleur de notre maison, et nous vous conseillerons ces activités ou lieux aux côtés desquels l'on passe lorsqu'on n'y est pas attentif. Nous n'attendons plus que vous ! :-)  nb: 2 chats dans la maison. Strictement limités au rez de chaussée. Pas d'accès aux chambres et étages supérieurs.

Ik spreek; NL - FR - TR - EN - PT  Mijn hobbies zijn reizen, fietsen, koken, zwemmen..  Ik ben verslaafd aan vintage spullen en pronkstukken uit de jaren zestig en zeventig...

Bonjour, L'accueil fait partie de nos priorités, la famille, les enfants, les amis, les hôtes... Nous avons à coeur d'ouvrir notre maison et notre table pour écouter, échanger, découvrir et faire découvrir.. Nous apprécions la bonne cuisine avec des produits de chez nous ou d'Italie en particulier, bios et de qualité. Nous aimons notre quartier vert et durable avec ses attraits exceptionnels, verger, potager, rucher... Voyager et communiquer dans d'autres langues est pour nous un plaisir , partir... ou rester mais toujours à la rencontre de l'autre.

From Southern Germany, workes for a blind expert on Digitising European Industry in the European Commission, interested in contemporary art, qigong (daoist tradition), gothic Cathedrals, Argentinian tango.
Infographiste, c'est la première fois que j' utilise Airbnb, j'aime bien le contact humain, j'espère avec cette aventure faire de belles rencontres humaines
Hi All! I am an Italian solitary wanderer currently living in Brussels! I love travelling, I am en hectic concerts/festivals attender, I like nature, seasons, laughing and enjoying each moment!

Hi,  We are a young happy belgian family who loves to travel. While we're not home, we like to let other people enjoy our home and get a real Brussels experience.  Hope you will like it :-)  Christophe, Marie and Charles

My boyfriend and I just bought an appartment in Antwerp. We both work in the city and we have a lot of friends living nearby, so we just love it here. I love to travel, meet people, learn languages, go out with friends, read, walk, swim, ... Me and my boyfriend traveled a lot (mostly in South America) and we learnt to appreciate a "warm" style of lodging: when discovering a city, it's nice to have a cosy, private place nearby and it's even nicer when you  have people who give you tips about the place and do their best to make you feel at home. Experiences like that made our own trips richer, so we want to pass this on to other people. We are more familiar with couchsurfing than with Airbnb, but we think this might be more our thing. Let us find out!

I'm 100% pure Belgian. Born and raised in Brussels in a wonderfull family. Did some scouting till 18 years and then did several sports. I love Kiting, Squach, Golf, Mountin bike and since a couple of years I'm a Rugby Coach. But my real passion is advertising. I'm an Art Director who worked in several advertising agencies. Today I live in this beautiful apartment partly with my lovely children.  I love making new contacts. Meeting people. Learning new things.  If you plan to come over to my place I would just ask you to bring something from your country. I'll show you brussels but I would love to know everything from your place.  Hope to meet you soon.  Henry.

After 15 years working abroad, I have just made my native Brussels my new homebase !  Happy to be back, in a nice new appartment, I travel a fair amount and am always happy to have other citizens of the world and enthousiastic AirBnB'ers enjoy my place whilst away. New to AirBnB, I have just loved the interactions with first visitors, and am very keen to share my (many) do's and (very few) dont's in this vibrant multi-cultural European capital

"Adventure is the best way to learn."  Hi everyone, My name is Christel and this is my story: I come from the countryside of Belgium. You know...like a small time-stood-still-village where everybody knows everybody :) ? Well, the only way to get out of there once in a while is by going to my favorite city in Belgium, Antwerp.  The City. I like art, no I mean I LOVE art. Music, theatre, ballet, expositions, literature, performances,...are my sources of inspiration to be creative. I also love  Antwerp is both modern and authentic. It’s a city that moves. There are dozens of cultural activities every week. The food in the restaurants, even in the tiny bars are amazing. It’s ALL about exploring with all your senses.   About the apartment. My husband, my kids and I renovated this building a couple of years ago. I prefer to stay there once in a while, having some time for myself. That’s why we decided it to rent it on Airbnb. We’ve chosen for this neighborhood ‘cause it’s the most upcoming place in Antwerp. It’s on a foot walk from the centre and yet it’s different. It’s Antwerps most multicultural neigbourhood. Over 70 different nationalities! And they all have their own cultural traditions which are awesome to discover!  To my guests. Enjoy your time in Antwerp, they say it's the city of diamonds.  But for me it's the people who shine :) Leave a note, a comment or better...a story before you leave.  I love stories.

We are a belgian family with 2 children, and this is the house where we live. We rent the house on Airbnb only the weeks we are on holiday. We love nature and nice atmosfeers. That's why we chose this place to live, at the border of the great "Forêt de Soignes". We couldn't live far away from everything, that's why we are only 2 steps far away from the center city. We love to share a good glass of wine with our friends, or to go for a hike in the forest. We also do a lot of activites with our children. We listen to jazz music and actual music, and our favorite filmakers are Clint Eastwood, and Jacques Audiard. One of the trips outside Brussels we love to do, is to go to the sea, at the border between France en Belgium: the beach is wild and facing a natural reserve. When we travel, we like to stay in a calm and confortable place, with old stones, and within a great nature. We appreciate if the host let us maps and informations about what to do in the area. It's even better if the host is there, and if we can have a nice discussion, and for instance share a local product. Nous sommes une famille belge avec 2 enfants et nous vivons dans cette maison que nous ne louons que 3 semaines, pendant que nous sommes en vacances. Nous aimons la nature, voilà pourquoi nous avons acheté cette maison au bord de la merveilleuse Forêt de Soignes. Nous ne pourrions pas vivre loin de tout, c'est pourquoi nous habitons près du centre ville de Bruxelles. Nous aimons partager un bon verre de vin avec nos amis ou partir en ballade en forêt. Nous faisons aussi beaucoup d'activités avec nos enfants. Nous écoutons du jazz ou de la musique actuelle et nos réalisateurs préférés sont Clint Eastwood et Jacques Audiard. L'une des escapades qu'on adore, c'est d'aller à la mer, à la frontière entre la Belgique et la France, où les plages sont sauvages face à u!ne réserve naturelle. Quand nous voyageons, nous aimons nous retrouver dans un endroit calme et confortable, dans de vieilles pierres, et une nature magnifique sur place.. Nous aimons que notre hôte nous ait laissé des cartes et indications sur les choses à faire et à voir. C'est encore mieux si nous pouvons le rencontrer et avoir une belle discussion, ou échanger des produits locaux.

Jeune musicienne, active dans le secteur culturel, toujours envieuse de nouvelles rencontres, et ouvertes à toutes discutions.  Je vous accueil avec plaisir dans mon petit appartement que je partage avec mon meilleur ami, Nicolas, lui aussi actif dans le secteur culturel.  A bientôt ! :)

Je suis juriste et coach sportive. Ayant un bel espace pour vivre, ce serait dommage de ne pas le partager avec ceux qui sont de passage dans notre capitale, que ce soit pour quelques jours ou une période de découverte un peu plus longue. A bientôt, en forme!
Frenchman living in Brussels for 5 years. Host on Airbnb mainly for the pleasure to welcome and the opportunity to meet people.

Mère de famille, enthousiaste et adore voyager. J'aime la ville de Bruxelles à la fois calme et animée cette ville offre toujours des nouveautés à découvrir. On y trouve de nombreuses expositions, de bons restaurants et de très belles promenades.

I am a belgian school teacher from Brussels. I am 31 years old. I speak french and english. I am used to travel. I have been traveling in south east Asia for 6 months and I done a year trip in New Zealand cycling around both islands. I have taught in Burkina Faso as well as in Sri Lanka for shorts periods. I like taking pictures, drama and read. I like writing, I am in a project writing children's books. I enjoy nature, hiking and cycling but I love city trips  visiting architecture and art museums  also. …
Plutôt cool et optimiste :)

I grew up in open houses and I'm delighted to share the house that I love with people who will appreciate its warmth and cosiness.  I'm a free-lance interpreter working mainly for the EU in Brussels.  I was born in Chile, grew up in Germany and Spain and have stayed for longer periods in many countries, including the US and Syria. In Brussels this is the run of the mill. That's maybe why it feels so much like home.  I have a passion for sailing (especially the Greek islands), creating beautiful images and tasty flavours and dancing to latin rhythms.  I love big open spaces and nature in general, be it in the ocean or the wilderness.
Hello,  I'm a young woman living and working in Brussels, a city I know very well and enjoy very much!  I am a regular user of Airbnb and look forward to hosting in Brussels!

Hi,   A Brussels born and based 29 years old, I travel a lot for work and for fun. I've lived for 3 years in the Democratic Republic of Congo doing social impact management. I'm also passionate about photography and attended a 6 weeks program at NYU about Photography & Human Rights organised by Magnum Foundation. I keep travelling for work and I'm happy to offer my lovely appartement when abroad on assignment.  If I'm here when you come, I would be very happy to welcome you and take the time to discuss and show you around. I usually travel light and love to get lost and take the time to talk to locals wherever I go to get a real sense of my destination.  My motto? Make people smile!

host_about: I wellcome you with pleasure in a nice recently renovated and independant flat at the ground floor of my house. I live in a quite residential area, just off a wonderful park, with very easy and fast connections with the centrum, the airport, the central station. I do my best to make your stay in Brussels pleasant and interesting !

URRENT MISSION  Don't cry because it's over, smile because it happened.  ABOUT ME  A small girl who wants to explore the big world!  I enjoy life in every way it's possible: traveling, cooking (and eating), drinking some good wine and beers, meeting new and interesting people, exploring myself, reading and writing, going to festivals and concerts, snowboarding, being active (or trying to be), taking pictures (because my memory is sooo bad),...  I'm a very happy person. Glad to be young!  INTERESTS  Photography, snowboarding, going out with friends, reading, enjoy good food and wine, nature, hiking, writing, cooking, music and festivals... ENJOY LIFE!  MUSIC, MOVIES & BOOKS  Movies: Moonrise Kingdom, Up, A Clockwork Orange, Amélie Poulain, The Curious Case of Benjamin Button, Finding Nemo, No country for old men, Into the wild, Black Swan, Eternal sunshine of a spotless mind, Django Unchained,...  Music: I like a lot of different kind of music. I really like to go festivals (and in special to Pukkelpop).  The XX, Eels, Mumford and Sons, Red Hot Chili Peppers, The Beatles, The Doors, Macy Gray, Isbells, Editors, Fleet Foxes, Ben Howard, Bon Iver, Foo fighters, Band of Skulls, Arctic Monkeys, Absynthe Minded, Vampire Weekend, The Vaccines, Tracy Chapman, Simon & Garfunkel, Queen of the Stone Ages, Oasis, The National, The Kinks, Kasabian, Johnny Cash, Gotye, Geppetto and the Whales, The Beach Boys, Arcade Fire, Sigur Ros, The Smiths, Massive Attack, Coely, Bonobo, Flume, Franz Ferdinand, Pixies, Band of Horses, Trixie Whitley, Brandom Flowers, MGMT, The Chemical Brothers, ...  ONE AMAZING THING I'VE DONE  - Roadtrip in Greece with three other friends  - Roadtrip France with seven other friends  - Lived for 9 weeks in Vancouver  - Roadtrip Vancouver Island by my own  - Roadtrip Rocky Mountains with my boyfriend  - Citytrips in Europe: Rome, Lissabon, Barcelona, London, Paris, Budapest, Amsterdam, Brussels,...  - Festivals in Belgium: Pukkelpop, Gentse Feesten, Rock Werchter, Dour, Les Ardents, Antilliaanse Feesten, Tomorrowland, Best Kept Secret (Netherlands),...  TEACH, LEARN, SHARE  Be grateful.  Be yourself.  Be happy.  ***  PHILOSOPHY  When I was 5 years old, my mother always told me that happiness was the key to life. When I went to school, they asked me what I wanted to be when I grew up. I wrote down 'happy'. They told me I didn't understand the assignment, and I told them they didn't understand life. -  John Lennon  Be happy and grateful with everything you have and get. I'm happy and grateful with everything I have and get!
Clémentine, 27 ans, française expatriée en Belgique, amoureuse du voyage et des découvertes !

Once upon a time, A few Kosmopolitan nomads were gathering around the fire in a circle. All coming from different places, cultures, backgrounds, goals, destiny,.. They were meeting at the crossroads and they were leaving in different directions. They just shared the same interest in telling their stories, their experiences and listen to others to enlarge their world. K-Nomadism philosophy is about  learning to unlearn; no ties with our beliefs system so we can discover the world around us as new. The shaman used to say "I have a vision, one day everybody will be able to travel and to discover other cultures, other people, other ways to look at the world. Those travelers will understand that we are all K-nomads because we are just passing through life; no one stay forever, just the moments we share exist." So enjoy the moment with us, unlearn around the circle of fire and see today as a new day.  Welcome into the K-Nomads tribe.

We are YawnSleep! Together we make YawnFamily... a community of friends.  My name is Eugène, I am the owner & initiator of YawnWorld.  Together with Masha & Mathieu we are ready to welcome you.  After having spent years traveling, living and working around the world for big corporate hotel chains it was time to start to do something that has a personality...and here we are, with YawnSleep. Why 'Yawn' people ask. We much felt that in today's world we are surrounded by a world of beige...things look more & more the same, with less & less personality.  Equally so Yawning adds oxygen to your blood, works contageous and creates new energy!  With Yawn's concept we believe in making your stay comfortable in a residential atmosphere...for short or long stay.  Our design style is a mix of vintage & modern.  We like to accessorize with art and books.  A certain lightness of being offering you a superbe Scandinavian bed to sleep in; German bedding and a wonderful cotton/linen blend of sheets.  A good shower and excellent WIFI. Most rooms have a kitchen or kitchenette. Come and try us out!  We'd love to have you stay with us and get your feedback on how we can do better!  In Yawn We Trust!

host_about: Passionné et curieux de tout, je suis  un fan  absolu de voyages et de grands espaces et je n'aime rien autant que partager un beau moment avec d'autres personnes autour d'un verre ou d'un bon repas. J'aime tout ce qui a attrait à la culture, aux arts et moyens d'expression comme la peinture, la littérature, la chanson, la photo, le cinéma ou même la danse, tout ce qui permet de s'exprimer et de s'élever. Je m'intéresse aussi  beaucoup à ce qui touche au développement personnel et à une certaine forme de spiritualité, comme la méditation , le yoga, la lecture,...

Hallo, ik ben Arthur en verhuur sinds een dik jaar een appartement op airbnb.  Aangezien ik meestal de organisator ben als we met vrienden op citytrip gaan, ben ik eveneens graag een goede host voor mijn gasten. Daarom sta ik altijd klaar met suggesties om jullie verblijf extra aangenaam te maken. Ik woon al meer dan 10 jaar in dezelfde buurt als het appartement, wat betekent dat ik snel in de buurt ben in geval van een probleempje, maar ook dat ik de buurt heel goed ken en voldoende tips kan geven wat betreft bezienswaardigheden en restaurantjes.  Het appartement is ruim en heeft een grote woonkamer met hoog plafond, wat ervoor zorgt dat het gezellig vertoeven is als je met een groep vrienden of met het gezin een weekend samen wilt doorbrengen. Het interieur is nogal eclectisch qua stijl, vintage gemixt met design klassiekers. Vooral geen zwart/wit, maar kleurrijk, en ook zo ingericht dat het lijkt alsof iemand er echt woont, geen steriele hotelkamer. Ik ben een liefhebber van films, fotografie en kunst, en dit valt eveneens als je het appartement betreedt. Litho's van Karel Appel en Dali worden afgewisseld met foto's van Helmut Newton en Herb Ritts.  Als ik zelf op citytrip ga, vind ik naast de huiselijkheid van het appartement dat ik huur, de locatie erg belangrijk. Daarom dat ik voor het appartement op Vleminckveld gekozen heb, het ligt recht in het midden van alle belangrijke attracties/buurten. Je kunt deze allemaal te voet bezoeken, het bruisende Zuid, het historisch centrum, het shopping gedeeltje,...  Het ligt dus enorm centraal en terrasjes en restaurantjes liggen zeer nabij, maar toch is de straat erg rustig, dus van nachtlawaai is geen sprake.  Niet te vergeten is de supermarkt die zich in hetzelfde gebouw bevindt, super handig als je last minute nog iets nodig hebt. Kortom ik heb geprobeerd alle elementen waar ikzelf belang aan hecht als ik op citytrip ga, te bundelen in het appartement dat ik verhuur in mijn thuishaven Antwerpen.

Hello, thanks for visiting our page and taking a moment of your time to look at our profile. As true citizens of Brussels we speak French, English, Dutch, German, Croatian, Serbian, Slovenian, Bosnian and a bit of Spanish.  We would be delighted to host you, give you advice and share our experience which will make your stay in Brussels with us unique and unforgettable.  Our beloved city is full of secret, hidden places far away from the tourist paths  only known by locals. It will be our pleasure to help you to discover these hidden gems that makes this city so unique and different from other capitals.  We love travelling, nature, all forms of artistic creation, enjoy fresh home made food and a healthy style of living. When we are at home we enjoy reading, listening to music, gardening or just relaxing in our nice house or drinking a good glass of wine on our terrasse with a view on our beautiful garden.  The evenings can be very quite here even if we are very close to the city center. You can hear the birds, from time to time see even a fox or enjoy the sunset from our terrace.  As we like ourselves discovering new places and meeting people from all over the world, we will be very happy to be your hosts to make you feel like at home in our house and tell you some interesting stories about places, people, habits in Belgium and abroad. Please do not hesitate to contact us if you have some more questions about your stay or ourselves. Hope to see you soon at our place! Kind regards. Leja, Dounia and Dominique

Hi! I'm Charlotte, I live in Antwerp, Belgium. I like to travel and to meet other people and cultures worldwide. I love cooking and I'm a diehard art-addict. :)
I absolutely love to entertain. wine and dine is the word and if I can do it whilst showing people the beautiful city I live in, why not?!

I'm a civil servant, working 9-5 and I'm fairly involved in the Brussels cultural scene. I'm also a freelance translator/subtitlor for a yearly "queer" film festival called Pink Screens. But I manage my time well, so I still have enough free time left to meet up and get to know people - and hosting them!   I have been living in Brussels - the capital of Europe! - for the last 17 years, and I am proud to introduce my city to visitors, because Brussels has a lot more to offer than most people know. I want you guys to leave satisfied!  As Brussels has many people living here for a limited period (to study, for tourism or business, ...) I've gotten the opportunity to make a lot of foreign friends. I have really enjoyed helping them to discover my city/country.  I do sports, not really for cosmetic reasons but to feel my body and relax my mind. My main interests are politics, languages, culture, traveling, reading on my Kindle, movies and music.  My favorite movie directors are Danny Boyle, Steven Spielberg and Alfred Hitchcock. Favorite writers include Eric-Emmanuel Schmitt, Nick Hornby and Flip Kowlier. Favorite musicians: way too much to make a fair list!

Mijn naam is Ine.  Sinds 20 jaar run ik mijn B&B en de beeldhouwerie in het hartje van de oude stad Antwerpen.   Met mijn partner en 3 zonen bewoon ik de 3de en 4de verdieping van ons huis, boven de beeldhouwerie, en boven de gastenkamers.   Lang geleden werkte ik enige jaren in toerisme, en heb dus ook wel wat gereisd.  Ooit was ik een echte kamperende rugzaktoerist.  Helaas gaat dat op een zeker moment fysiek niet meer zo goed.  Nu kies ik al reizend voor iets meer comfort...  Ik vind het leuk om gasten te ontvangen, ook gezinnen met kinderen.   Toen ik zelf jaren achter elkaar in hotels woonde, miste ik het huiselijk gevoel, zelf een ei kunnen bakken, mijn bed opmaken zoals ikzelf dat wilde... Daarom is het logies bij mij precies zoals ik het zelf het liefste zou willen : je eigen klein plekje, waar jij je spullen legt zoals je het zelf leuk vindt, en niemand die komt herschikken of jouw rommel opruimt. In je eigen mini-keukenhoek, kan je snel een  soepje brouwen, of uren koffie drinken met je lief, in je pyjama met een zachtgekookt eitje, aan het open raam van de binnenkoer.. .  Ik hou van een hartelijke vrije sfeer : iedereen is aangenaam voor elkaar, maar laat elkaar met rust.  Zo ontstaan contacten vanuit zichzelf, ongeforceerd.  Gras groeit niet door aan de sprieten te trekken, maar door de wortels water te geven.

I'm 29 years old, study Language and Literature at UA and work part-time in Antwerp.  I love the lively atmosphere of every city and try to enjoy it as much as possible. Going from concerts at festivals or parks, fashion and shopping, theatre performances, museums or just strolling through the city. And since I'm very social and quick to make contacts, the vision of an AirBnB is right up my alley. Providing a cosy space for wanderlust travelers, handing information about my town and creating some interaction without obtrusiveness. So travelling  in an unconventional way and interacting with locals is something the guests and I have in common. After travelling to San Francisco to live with a childhood friend, participating on an intercultural project in Mexico, sharing the apartment of an inhabitant in Berlin, Valladolid, Barcelona, Vienna, etc I even try to make a holiday out of being at home. Or as one of my favorite Dutch writers, Godfriend Bomans,  would put it; "The art of living is to be at home when one is travelling". I hope to bring my guests a feeling of "Home" during their stay and hopefully soon I'll meet and welcome you in Antwerp, I'm looking forward to it.  Ik ben  29 jaar, werk parttime en studeer  taal- en letterkunde aan de Universiteit van Antwerpen. Ik hou erg  van het levendige en bruisende, dat elke stad in zich heeft en probeer daar zoveel mogelijk van te genieten:  de terrasjes, optredens in parken of festivals, shoppen,   theatervoorstellingen, musea, flaneren door de stad, noem maar op.  Vermits ik vrij sociaal ben en snel  contacten maak, past de AirBnB -formule  helemaal in mijn visie: een cosy plek verschaffen aan de reislustige gasten, hen informatie geven over mijn stad en enige interactie opbouwen zonder opdringerigheid. Eén punt hebben de gasten en ik gemeen: we reizen graag, doen dit graag op een niet al te conventionele manier en houden van interactie met de plaatselijke inwoner(s).  Zo ging ik naar San Francisco om bij een jeugdvriendin in te wonen, nam deel aan een intercultureel project in Mexico,  deelde het appartement van een inwoonster in  Berlijn, Valladolid, Barcelona en Wenen, enz.  Ik probeer me ook thuis op reis te voelen of zoals de Nederlandse schrijver Godfried Bomans, één mijn favoriete schrijvers, het stelde : ” De kunst van te leven is thuis te zijn alsof men op reis is ". Ik hoop dat ik mijn gasten een gevoel van 'thuis zijn'  tijdens hun reis kan geven en hoop jullie snel te mogen verwelkomen en ontmoeten in Antwerpen..Ik kijk er alvast naar uit..  Tengo 29 años y estudio Lengua y Literatura en la Universidad de Amberes y trabajo a medio tiempo en la ciudad. Me encanta el ambiente animado de cada ciudad y trato de disfrutarlo lo más posible con paseos a conciertos en festivales o parques, a través de la moda y las compras, obras de teatro, museos o simplemente pasear por la ciudad. Como soy una persona muy social y que rápidamente hace contactos, la visión de Airbnb es lo mío. Ofrezco un espacio agradable para los viajeros con deseo de explorar, facilito información sobre mi ciudad y establezco algún tipo de interacción sin impertinencia. Viajar de una manera poco convencional e interactuar con la gente local, es algo que los clientes y yo tenemos en común. Después de haber viajado a la ciudad de San Francisco para vivir con una amiga de la infancia, participado en un proyecto intercultural en México, compartido el apartamento de un habitante de Berlín, Valladolid, Barcelona, Viena, y más lugar, hasta trato de hacer unas vacaciones estando en mi casa. Como dice uno de mis escritores Neerlandés favoritos, Godfried Bomans "el arte de vivir es estar en casa cuando uno está viajando." Espero darles a mis invitados una sensación de "hogar" durante su estancia y espero que pronto pueda darle la bienvenida en Amberes.  我今年 29歲,在UA修語言及文學,同時在安特衛普打工。我喜歡每一個城市的熱鬧氛圍,不管是音樂節,公園演唱會,時尚購物,戲劇表演,博物館,或在市中心散步,我都盡可能找機會品嘗。另外我很樂於交朋友,不管是提供舒適的空間給旅遊愛好者,傳達關於我的城市的資訊,或無壓力的互動,我很理解也能夠發揮Airbnb想表達的精神,畢竟非凡的旅遊方式和與當地人交集是我們的共同點。 我曾去舊金山與兒時的朋友居住,參與過墨西哥的多重文化案子,與他人居住的城市包含柏林,巴拉多利德,巴塞羅那,維也納,等等。在家時我也儘量保持旅遊的心態。我最愛的荷蘭作家『Godfriend Bomans』曾說:『生活的祕訣在於旅遊時也感受到家。』我希望來這裡的客人都有這樣的感受,並期待很快能歡迎您來安特衛普。   我今年29岁,在UA修语言及文学,同时在安特卫普打工。我喜欢每一个城市的热闹氛围,不管是音乐节,公园演唱会,时尚购物,戏剧表演,博物馆,或在市中心散步,我都尽可能找机会品尝。另外我很乐于交朋友,不管是提供舒适的空间给旅游爱好者,传达关于我的城市的资讯,或无压力的互动,我很理解也能够发挥Airbnb想表达的精神,毕竟非凡的旅游方式和与当地人交集是我们的共同点。 我曾去旧金山与儿时的朋友居住,参与过墨西哥的多重文化案子,与他人居住的城市包含柏林,巴拉多利德,巴塞罗那,维也纳,等等。在家时我也尽量保持旅游的心态。我最爱的荷兰作家『Godfriend Bomans』曾说:『生活的秘诀在于旅游时也感受到家。 』我希望来这里的客人都有这样的感受,并期待很快能欢迎您来安特卫普。

Viajar de una manera poco convencional e interactuar con la gente local, es algo que los clientes y yo tenemos en común. Después de haber viajado a la ciudad de San Francisco para vivir con una amiga de la infancia, participado en un proyecto intercultural en México, compartido el apartamento de un habitante de Berlín, Valladolid, Barcelona, Viena, y más lugar, hasta trato de hacer unas vacaciones estando en mi casa. Como dice uno de mis escritores Neerlandés favoritos, Godfried Bomans "el arte de vivir es estar en casa cuando uno está viajando." Espero darles a mis invitados una sensación de "hogar" durante su estancia y espero que pronto pueda darle la bienvenida en Amberes.  我今年 29歲,在UA修語言及文學,同時在安特衛普打工。我喜歡每一個城市的熱鬧氛圍,不管是音樂節,公園演唱會,時尚購物,戲劇表演,博物館,或在市中心散步,我都盡可能找機會品嘗。另外我很樂於交朋友,不管是提供舒適的空間給旅遊愛好者,傳達關於我的城市的資訊,或無壓力的互動,我很理解也能夠發揮Airbnb想表達的精神,畢竟非凡的旅遊方式和與當地人交集是我們的共同點。 我曾去舊金山與兒時的朋友居住,參與過墨西哥的多重文化案子,與他人居住的城市包含柏林,巴拉多利德,巴塞羅那,維也納,等等。在家時我也儘量保持旅遊的心態。我最愛的荷蘭作家『Godfriend Bomans』曾說:『生活的祕訣在於旅遊時也感受到家。』我希望來這裡的客人都有這樣的感受,並期待很快能歡迎您來安特衛普。   我今年29岁,在UA修语言及文学,同时在安特卫普打工。我喜欢每一个城市的热闹氛围,不管是音乐节,公园演唱会,时尚购物,戏剧表演,博物馆,或在市中心散步,我都尽可能找机会品尝。另外我很乐于交朋友,不管是提供舒适的空间给旅游爱好者,传达关于我的城市的资讯,或无压力的互动,我很理解也能够发挥Airbnb想表达的精神,毕竟非凡的旅游方式和与当地人交集是我们的共同点。 我曾去旧金山与儿时的朋友居住,参与过墨西哥的多重文化案子,与他人居住的城市包含柏林,巴拉多利德,巴塞罗那,维也纳,等等。在家时我也尽量保持旅游的心态。我最爱的荷兰作家『Godfriend Bomans』曾说:『生活的秘诀在于旅游时也感受到家。 』我希望来这里的客人都有这样的感受,并期待很快能欢迎您来安特卫普。

So I’m a 29 years old Belgian guy … Here is the usual Bio I give for the event I organize :  Multilingual and strong interest in multinational environments, Nicolas joined BioLog Europe in January 2012 as a business developer for the American Market. Prior to this, Nicolas worked for MGA Conway in 2010 and served as a project coordinator to analyze the potential market and develop a structure in Shanghai for the Belgian Based consultancy company. Mr. Cogneau earned a Master of Human Resources Management from the Solvay Business School at the University of Brussels and a Bachelor of Sociology/Anthropology degree from the Catholic University of Louvain-la-Neuve (Belgium). He is also graduated from the University of Cape Town where he did a postgraduate diploma in management at the faculty of Commerce. In the last 4 years, he lived 6 months in Spain (in the continuation of his Master), 5 months in China, 1 year in South Africa and he is currently living in between Belgium & the United States.     I was 10 months in the states last year and now I have to return for 3 months (2 in NYC & & in California). My job is trying to help life sciences companies to expand their business in Europe by promoting Belgium as an ideal location. So basically I’m calling/sending mail to companies to understand their needs & see if they have projects in theirs pipes. I’m also travelling extendedly to attend fairs & other investments seminars on the life science industry.    Behind that, I’m a straight men who doesn’t smoke … I love discovering new places & meet new people … Discuss about everything and really easy going ! I’m also a bit maniac about where I live (due to the fact that I’m travelling a lot, I love to have to feeling to be “at home” when I’m in a place … Something quiet/cozy/relax). I also enjoy being into the wild … going outside for a walk, a run …  Nicolas.

Amo viaggiare nei Paesi meno conosciuti, perchè ho scoperto che spesso sono i più interessanti e memorabili; mi piace leggere, soprattutto narrativa, ma non disdegno altri generi; ascolto molta musica, quasi tutta in vinile perchè mi piace il loro suono e gli oggetti in sè, li trovo "caldi", da tutti i punti di vista.  Il mio stile di viaggio è aperto al prossimo, desideroso di conoscere al meglio i luoghi, al di là delle vetrine offerte dalle guide di viaggio e la cosa che preferisco del viaggiare in moto è che posso scegliere i miei tempi e le destinazioni con la massima libertà. Português Depois de ter viajado em diversos países e ter se hospedado em vários tipos de hospedagens diferente, um jovem viajante, mudou-se para Bruxelas, onde ele reconhece a cidade como um dos melhores locais do mundo e ponto de partida para iniciar uma boa aventura na famosa Europa. A proposta é muito simples: entrar a fundo, aproveitar ao máximo sua viagem tão sonhada. Não perdendo tempo em busca de informações de trajetos de metrô, bus, trens etc., não desperdiçando dinheiro com hotéis onde você só chegará para dormir e tomar um café da manhã quando der tempo. O viajante pode optar por um roteiro completo onde ele você cairá dentro do dia a dia de um europeu. Levaremos você para os principais pontos turísticos de uma forma prática e rápida, mostraremos as melhores baladas, bares e aonde o verdadeiro espírito europeu bomba na noitada europeia. Faremos roteiros com bate e volta entre outros países como Holanda, França, Espanha, Alemanha etç;; Faremos você se sentir "Chez Toi" Temos diversos serviços e preços a oferecer, tudo vai depender do quão intenso você quer vivenciar essa viagem.  FRANCES Après avoir voyagé dans de nombreux pays et ont séjourné dans une variété de logements, un jeune voyageur, a déménagé à Bruxelles, où il reconnaît la ville comme l'un des meilleurs endroits du monde et le point de départ pour commencer une bonne aventure célèbre l'Europe. La proposition est très simple: entrer dans le fond, tirer le meilleur parti de votre voyage tant rêvé. Sans perdre de temps à chercher des itinéraires de métro de l'information, bus, trains, etc., ne pas gaspiller l'argent sur les hôtels où vous venez dormir et venez prendre un petit déjeuner quand vous avez le temps. Le voyageur peut opter pour un script complet dans lequel il vous tomberez dans la vie quotidienne d'un Européen. Nous vous emmenons aux principaux sites touristiques dans une pratique et rapide, nous montrerons les meilleures ballades, des bars et où le véritable esprit de la pompe européenne dans la soirée européenne. Nous allons faire des scripts avec d'autres Rebond des pays tels que la Hollande, la France, l'Espagne, l'Allemagne etc ;; Nous vous faire sentir « Chez Toi » Nous avons plusieurs services et les prix à offrir, tout dépendra de la façon dont vous voulez faire l'expérience intense de ce voyage.
